main event: An observer watched a circular shaped yellow-orange colored object over Duluth, Minnesota on 24 Feb 67.
interesting points: The object appeared to approach the observer and faded after about 5 minutes., The weather was clear, allowing for a good view against a dark background., The object emitted no noise during the sighting., The description matches that of an astronomical observation, possibly Venus, which was visible on that date., The observer, a welder, used binoculars for a clearer view of the object.
witness description: 52-year-old welder from Clide Iron Works in Duluth
